      <title>Strength Training for Runners – Accomplishing It in Seven Ways</title>
      <link>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/strength-training-for-runners-accomplishing-it-in-seven-ways/</link>
      <comments>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/strength-training-for-runners-accomplishing-it-in-seven-ways/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Jun 2012 12:05:54 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>seniortrainer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Health and Fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[marathon training]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[running tips]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/strength-training-for-runners-accomplishing-it-in-seven-ways/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;More than losing, being unable to finish the race is very painful to any runner. Even though we deny it, this scenario really happens to those who lack the strength, endurance, stamina, and performance. This is what strength training for runners is trying to combat. Moreover, it uplifts the fact that anyone who desires to [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/"&gt;Exercises For The Elderly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-seniors-have-fun-exercises-for-the-elderly/How_Seniors_Have_Fun-_Exercises_for_The_Elderly-Strength_Training_for_Runners__Accomplishing_It_in_Seven_Ways.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>More than losing, being unable to finish the race is very painful to any runner. Even though we deny it, this scenario really happens to those who lack the strength, endurance, stamina, and performance. This is what strength training for runners is trying to combat. Moreover, it uplifts the fact that anyone who desires to finish the race can achieve so if he gets properly trained using <a href="http://www.marathon-training-tips.com/running-tips.html" target='_blank'>running tips</a> today.</p>
<p>The said program is composed of other vital exercises that can keep marathon participants all fired up for the big event. They are designed to keep the different muscles of the body in tough shape so as to withstand long running distances. </p>
<p>Kettlebell Long Cycles: As the name suggests, this exercise needs a pair of Kettlebells. Lifting them up to a certain height repeatedly helps develop strong hips, glutes, core muscles, shoulders, and overall cardiovascular conditioning.</p>
<p>Cycling: Cycling strengthens quadriceps, shins, calf muscles, and hamstrings. It is a strength training workout that reduces the athlete&rsquo;s susceptibility to injury. This is due to the fact that cycling strengthens the connective tissue of the hip, knee, and ankle regions that are often overused when running.</p>
<p>Swimming: Swimming exercises seem to be a part of very training program for athletes of different sports. It has the capacity to toughen the muscles through repeated strokes in water while muscular pains are being pacified. Overall, swimming improves a runner&rsquo;s flexibility, breathing and oxygen-holding capacity.</p>
<p>Deep Water Running: This exercise is aimed at making the muscles stand jerks and shocks that might be experienced on ground. It doesn&rsquo;t keep the muscle from getting strained. Rather it makes the muscles cope with it with the ease of water. This is why it also advised as therapy for people who need to recover from injuries aside from following correct <a href="http://www.marathon-training-tips.com/" target='_blank'>marathon training</a>. Belts and vests are the gears you will need for this water activity.</p>
<p>Use Of Elliptical Trainer: Elliptical trainers are used in the strength training for runners because they allow movements that make the major muscles of the body work simultaneously just like what happens in an actual marathon. With just one equipment, you can experience movements in skiing, hiking and mountain climbing among others.</p>
<p>Use Of Rowing Machines: Exercising on this equipment can result to strengthened quadriceps, buttocks, hips, and upper body. When the lower body is getting tired towards the end of the race, having a strong upper body could be very beneficial. When you have properly trained in the rowing machine, your arms, necks and shoulders would be more than capable of &lsquo;carrying&rsquo; you when your almost drained to cross the finish line.</p>
<p>Running Uphill: Running on flat surfaces results to easy running. This the type of running anyone who wants to win the race must cling on to. It engages the same sets of muscles disregarding the quads, hamstrings, glutes and calves. Strength training for runners on hills can focus on the development of the said muscles so that they could run longer distances faster using cross country running tips today.</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/">Exercises For The Elderly</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
