      <title>Reading Park Exercise</title>
      <link>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/reading-park-exercise/</link>
      <comments>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/reading-park-exercise/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 May 2012 13:02:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>seniortrainer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Health and Fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[park fitness in reading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[reading fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[reading park fitness]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/reading-park-exercise/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Get outside this summer season to workout with Peak XV Boot Camps and join their Reading Park Fitness sessions. Their outside boot camp sessions take place in Christchurch Meadows in Caversham which is beautifully set on the River Thames near the centre of Caversham. Their Park Fitness sessions in Reading are attended by up to [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/"&gt;Exercises For The Elderly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-seniors-have-fun-exercises-for-the-elderly/How_Seniors_Have_Fun-_Exercises_for_The_Elderly-Reading_Park_Exercise.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Get outside this summer season to workout with Peak XV Boot Camps and join their Reading Park Fitness sessions. Their outside boot camp sessions take place in Christchurch Meadows in Caversham which is beautifully set on the River Thames near the centre of Caversham. Their Park Fitness sessions in Reading are attended by up to 15 local women who spend an hour getting put through their paces by Peak XV Fitness instructors.</p>
<p>The sessions contain different boot camp style exercise routines such as running, jumping, body weight exercises and stretching. The sessions are sixty minutes long and run 4 occasions a week. A lot of the members prefer the outside atmosphere in which to exercise as they spend most of the remainder of their lives indoors. That is 1 of the primary appeals of the park fitness sessions run by Peak XV Fitness. Outdoor exercising sessions have grown in reputation over the past five years and Peak XV Fitness run many centres in the area.</p>
<p>Results that can be anticipated are up to 10 pounds of fat reduction in less than 28 days. Also members usually lose many inches off their waist and hips in the same time frame. The courses come with total nutritional assistance in the shape of weekly meal plans, recipes and nutritional supplements which are developed by a highly competent Nutritional Therapist. Members commonly join for three months but can opt for an on going month to month membership. Some of the members of the <a href="http://www.peakxvfitness.com/exercise/reading-fitness-classes" target='_blank'>the outdoor group</a> have been attending the sessions for more than a year now and have the benefits to show for it, feeling fitter and lighter than they have in years.</p>
<p>As the Spring brings in the lighter evenings much more men and women are getting outside to execute their exercise sessions. Basically <a href="http://www.peakxvfitness.com/bootcamps-reading" target='_blank'>group fitness sessions</a> in local parks are specifically common with female participants who make up the majority of Peak XV Fitness&rsquo;s clients. The women especially appreciate the group atmosphere and the assistance and encouragement the group brings. The women are usually nearby Mums or workers of nearby Caversham firms and come from all walks of life.</p>
<p>For a no cost 1 week trial at the gorgeous Caversham location in Christchurch Meadows contact boot camp director Chris Hines on 07879 646969 or register at their website.</p>
<p>Places are strictly limited and you may possibly want to book your spot ahead of time. Do not miss out on your opportunity to join Peak XV Fitness&rsquo;s really popular Reading Park Fitness this summer season.</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/">Exercises For The Elderly</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
