      <title>3 Vital Symptoms of High Blood Pressure</title>
      <link>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/3-vital-symptoms-of-high-blood-pressure/</link>
      <comments>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/3-vital-symptoms-of-high-blood-pressure/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 May 2012 13:40:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>seniortrainer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Health and Fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[health]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[High Blood Pressure]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/3-vital-symptoms-of-high-blood-pressure/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;High blood pressure is a dangerous condition with a variety of symptoms, that can only be verified through a check of your blood pressure. Nevertheless, there are certain factors that can make it more likely that you will develop high blood pressure, and sometimes there are symptoms you can recognize as well. If you happen [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/"&gt;Exercises For The Elderly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-seniors-have-fun-exercises-for-the-elderly/How_Seniors_Have_Fun-_Exercises_for_The_Elderly-3_Vital_Symptoms_of_High_Blood_Pressure.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>High blood pressure is a dangerous condition with a variety of symptoms, that can only be verified through a check of your blood pressure. Nevertheless, there are certain factors that can make it more likely that you will develop high blood pressure, and sometimes there are symptoms you can recognize as well. If you happen to notice any of the symptoms we discuss in this article for hypertension be sure to talk to your doctor.</p>
<p>Unfortunately experts can&#8217;t agree what high blood pressure is. Most are aware that blood pressure is a combination of two numbers called systolic pressure and diastolic pressure. There is often disagreement about numbers that are lower than 140/90, it is commonly believed that anything over that is hypertension. For instance if your blood pressure reading was 130/85, until recently it would have been considered normal. Now a reading of 120/80 or below is normal and many experts would call the previous reading as prehypertension. Your doctor may believe differently, a blood pressure reading above 120/80 should be cause for you adding exercise to your routine, as well as monitoring your diet. You could possibly glance into Feel Healthy.</p>
<p>Many people go through symptoms of high blood pressure even if they don&#8217;t actually suffer from hypertension. This happens because blood pressure is always raising and lowering&#8211;it changes depending on your activity and emotional levels. This is why you aren&#8217;t able to determine whether or not you have high blood pressure from a single measurement. When you monitor your blood pressure by yourself you need to make sure that you take your readings after a few minutes of rest and that you avoid caffeine for at least an hour before you do the reading. Even when medical professionals do your reading, you will have to have several done if you want to get a proper assessment. While nobody&#8217;s blood pressure stays constantly at a single level, having a healthy blood pressure level means that the readings stay within a &#8220;normal&#8221; range.</p>
<p>If high blood pressure is not controlled, it can lead to something called malignant hypertension, which is extremely high blood pressure. You might not have had noticeable symptoms when your blood pressure was only a little bit high, if you have malignant hypertension your symptoms are extreme and can include vomiting, nausea, dizziness and pain around your eyes. Losing consciousness is also a possibility in some cases. Some cases of malignant hypertension can come around out of nowhere but usually it is caused by someone neglecting to treat their only slightly elevated high blood pressure. If you start to display symptoms of malignant hypertension go to the doctor immediately. Studies have proved that high blood pressure usually results in erectile dysfunction. However what is more upsetting is the truth that the medicines taken to cure high blood pressure also leads to erectile dysfunction therefore making things worse for adult men. On the contrary there&#8217;s certainly no need to fear. You could merely glance into <a href="http://www.sildenafilcitrates.net" target="_blank">sildenafil citrate</a> and get treatments to your issues.</p>
<p>It is highly unlikely that you will show symptoms in the early stage of this common problem of high blood pressure. Regardless if you show signs or symptoms you should check your blood pressure on a regular basis, and it is more important for you to do so if you have a medical history of the disease or and of these risk factors. It is always better to be safe and get regular check-ups, whether you have the above mentioned symptoms of blood pressure or not.</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/">Exercises For The Elderly</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
