    <item>
      <title>The Reasons Your Heart Requires Cardiovascular Fitness</title>
      <link>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/the-reasons-your-heart-requires-cardiovascular-fitness/</link>
      <comments>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/the-reasons-your-heart-requires-cardiovascular-fitness/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 May 2012 13:54:28 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>seniortrainer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Health and Fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Cardio]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[exercise]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Heart]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/the-reasons-your-heart-requires-cardiovascular-fitness/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;It is a well-known reality that heart disease is one of the major causes of death around the world. In a long-term analysis on the health of the people in the United States, the U.S. Public Health Service documented the probabilities of developing heart problems with diverse groups in the populace. They have identified some [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/"&gt;Exercises For The Elderly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-seniors-have-fun-exercises-for-the-elderly/How_Seniors_Have_Fun-_Exercises_for_The_Elderly-The_Reasons_Your_Heart_Requires_Cardiovascular_Fitness.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It is a well-known reality that heart disease is one of the major causes of death around the world. In a long-term analysis on the health of the people in the United States, the U.S. Public Health Service documented the probabilities of developing heart problems with diverse groups in the populace. They have identified some high-risk groups.</p>
<p>Among the highest are males over 35 years old. If they are also cigarette smokers, have high blood pressure, have high levels of certain blood fats, and also have a family history of cardio disorders, these all will boost their likelihood of getting heart disease.</p>
<p>Other research workers have added to this list one more hazardous factor: the compulsive, hard-driving, extremely anxious character. The larger the severity, the greater the individual&#8217;s general danger. The risks to the heart can be separated into two main categories: those that are outside individual control, like heredity, sex and age, and the ones that can be controlled, avoided, and even eradicated. Among those within the second group will be what cardiologists refer to as &#8220;the triple threat.&#8221; They are the high blood pressure, cigarette smoking, plus high cholesterol levels individuals.</p>
<p>So let&#8217;s say you aspire to quickly get on the healthy side on the statistical ledger. The very first thing to undertake immediately will be to end the damaging behavior that got you in the difficulty you are in. Stop smoking and altering your diet immediately is going to start you over the correct path, but that&#8217;s just a start. Think of what a lifetime of abusing your heart has done to it.</p>
<p>Your heart is a muscle, or more accurately a bunch or &#8220;package&#8221; of muscle tissue, comparable in some ways to the muscles of the legs and arms. And just as working out strengthens then improves muscles in the limbs, it strengthens the health of the heart muscles as well. To make possible the injured heart to heal physically, different small blood vessels are going to form to transfer the load from injured blood vessels. This is known as collateral circulation. When the new network takes on enough of the function of the injured or narrowed blood vessels, a heart attack could be averted. Some experiments showed that moderate working out several times a week is more valuable for building up these auxiliary pathways than <a href="http://muscle4weightloss.com/high-intensity-workout/" target='_blank'>High Intensity Exercises</a> accomplished as often.</p>
<p>Ever since World War II, some large-scale statistical reports have evaluated the relationship with cardiovascular disease and physical activity.  A well-known survey compared 31,000 drivers and conductors of some bus companies. The more sedentary drivers had a significantly higher rate of heart problems than the conductors, who walked around the buses as well as climbed stairs onto the higher level. There have been several other studies that support this data.</p>
<p>The overall rule is that working out assists you to lessen the risk of damage to the heart. Some researches further attested the connection with working out and a healthy heart from the following findings: non-exercisers had a 49% greater danger of heart attack than the others included within the study. The investigation attributed 33% of that risk to sedentary habits alone.  Consequently, by employing the <a href="http://healtheybalanceddiet.com/interval-cardio-training/" target='_blank'>Interval Cardio Training</a>, you can entirely assume positive results not only for areas that concerns your cardio system but on the general status of your quality of life as well.</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/">Exercises For The Elderly</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
