      <title>Pool Exercise to Get in Shape</title>
      <link>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/pool-exercise-to-get-in-shape/</link>
      <comments>http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/pool-exercise-to-get-in-shape/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 26 May 2012 14:09:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>seniortrainer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Health and Fitness]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[elderly]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[exercise]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[exercises for the elderly]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/health-and-fitness/pool-exercise-to-get-in-shape/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Swimming is recognised as probably the most generally beneficial forms of exercise. The UK government have even taken steps to encourage everybody to get into swimming by reducing the charges at municipal swimming baths. Swimming is great for everybody, young and old. Since body weight in water is only around one tenth of waht it [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/"&gt;Exercises For The Elderly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-seniors-have-fun-exercises-for-the-elderly/How_Seniors_Have_Fun-_Exercises_for_The_Elderly-Pool_Exercise_to_Get_in_Shape.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Swimming is recognised as probably the most generally beneficial forms of exercise. The UK government have even taken steps to encourage everybody to get into swimming by reducing the charges at municipal swimming baths.</p>
<p>Swimming is great for everybody, young and old. Since body weight in water is only around one tenth of waht it is in air aqua aerobics is particularly good for those who are overweight.</p>
<p>Regular swimming will build endurance and does a lot for the cardiovascular system. It is an ideal form of exercise for pregnant women, those with back pain or arthritis.</p>
<p>Your body is so much lighter in water making it an excellent way to work of those accumulated excess pounds. Aqua aerobics and aqua exercise have been growing in popularity as awareness of the need to maintain a healthy weight also grows. Aqua aerobics imposes less impact on the joints and this helps you to exercise for longer. In a 30 minute workout you can expect to burn around 300 calories.</p>
<p>Aqua exercises are generally aimed at improving strength and mobility by using the resistance of the water. The cushioning effect of water makes this form of exercise particularly suitable for elderly people, those who are over weight and pregnant women.</p>
<p>If you are lucky enough to own your own <a href="http://www.1st-direct.com/">swimming pool</a> then you have a ready made environment that is ideal for water based exercise. The trick with any form of exercise is to start very gently indeed. Less is more as they say. The crucial thing in your early sessions is to not put yourself off by overdoing it. The first few sessions should be all about getting into the new routine of regular exercise.</p>
<p>Try starting gently by walking or even jogging in the water and maybe make it a social occasion by inviting friends or family to join you. In fact you are far more likely to stick to your new exercise regime if you have an exercise buddy to do it with you.</p>
<p> I recommend a good <a href="http://www.1st-direct.com/above-ground-pools.htm">above ground pool</a> in your own back garden if you really want to make the most of aqua exercise.</p>
<p></p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://exercisesfortheelderly.org/">Exercises For The Elderly</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
